osted on GitHub, and provides several librairies for your needs."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"These librairies help to split products and make users able to select only what they need.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SwiftUI is the only official supported framework.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"hero","backgroundImage":"ic_unified_ds.png","xcodeRequirement":"Xcode 26","chapter":"Import of the Swift Package and choose its librairies","title":"Swift Package integration"},{"kind":"tasks","tasks":[{"stepsSection":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using Xcode, in your "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"project package dependencies","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":", add a new ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"dependency","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Search with the GitHub repository URL (https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios), and select the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"ouds-ios","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" dependency."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can then choose the "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"dependency rule","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" you want."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To know which version you need, you can have a look on the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/wiki\/01-%E2%80%90-Available-API"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and also the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/releases"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"media":"tutorial-1-ouds-swift-package.png","caption":[],"code":null,"type":"step","runtimePreview":null},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Once you downloaded the package, you will see several librairies are available.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"They can be embeded inside your ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"target"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" librairies.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Things are separated to let users integrate only what they need and embed the abre minimum of content.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesContract","type":"text"}]},{"text":" library provides the main elements like the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSThemeableView"},{"text":". The theme contract is defined inside it.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSThemesOrange"}]},{"text":" provides the theme implementation for the Orange products, and contains also assets and all tokens for this theme.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSThemesSosh"}]},{"text":" provides the theme implementation for the Sosh products, and contains also assets and all tokens for this theme.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSThemesWireframe"}]},{"text":" provides the theme implementation for the Wireframe theme, which is a theme dedicated to mockups and prototypes.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools","type":"text"}]},{"text":" provides the theme implementation for the Orange products but with constraints of sizes and spaces.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSComponents"}]},{"type":"text","text":" contains the SwiftUI OUDS components defined with the Figma specifications, and also useful view modifers."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSTokensRaw","type":"text"}]},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSTokensSemantic","type":"text"}]},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSTokensComponents","type":"text"}]},{"text":" are librairies defining and providing the tokens for low level (raw),","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"middle level (semantic) or component levels (high level).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSModules","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" is for modules or rich components with extra logic.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSFoundations"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" is dedicated to some utilities and shared logic.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"step","caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add for example only the umbrella product merging all products mentioned above: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSSwiftUI","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"}]}],"code":null,"media":"tutorial-1-ouds-libraries.png","runtimePreview":null}],"anchor":"Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries","contentSection":[{"kind":"contentAndMedia","mediaPosition":"trailing","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS for iOS is an open source Swift Package available on GitHub under MIT license."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The package and the librairies must be added through Xcode.","type":"text"}]}]}],"title":"Import the Swift Package and the libraries"}]},{"anchor":"Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessments","assessments":[{"type":"multiple-choice","title":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Which of these choices is correct?"}]}],"choices":[{"isCorrect":true,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"I can contribute to OUDS using pull request"}]}],"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS is open source, under MIT license, and hosted on GitHub. Of course you can contribute!"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS supports officialy all Apple OS like visionOS, tvOS, watchOS, iPadOS, iOS and also CarPlay.","type":"text"}]}],"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The main supported targets are iOS \/ iPadOS. However we do our best to support macOS, visionOS, tvOS and watchOS.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"CarPlay specific cases are not scoped yet.","type":"text"}]}]},{"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS supports officialy only SwiftUI. UIKit is very experimental and not recommended."}]}],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS provides UIKit components","type":"text"}]}]}],"content":[]},{"type":"multiple-choice","content":[],"title":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Which imports of the OUDS Swift Package products can I choose?"}]}],"choices":[{"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can import all products provided by the Swift Package, and tailor your choice to keep only the ones needed.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Even if we recommend to choose only the atomic products you need, the ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" product wraps all of them.","type":"text"}]}],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some of the available products depending to my needs, or only "},{"code":"OUDSSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if I am very lazy and don’t care about my app size.","type":"text"}]}],"isCorrect":true},{"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You need to chose the products the Swift package provides","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"None, only the Swift package dependency matter"}]}],"isCorrect":false}]}]},{"kind":"callToAction","action":{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-2-instanciate-theme","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get started"}],"isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Get started"},"featuredEyebrow":"Tutorial","title":"Instanciate and inject a theme","abstract":[{"text":"The theme is exposed as one object which will be injected inside your SwiftUI view.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The theme provides all tokens which defines in the end the rendering of everything.","type":"text"}]}],"metadata":{"role":"project","categoryPathComponent":"Table-Of-Contents","category":"Orange Unified Design System","title":"Swift Package integration"},"kind":"project","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/Table-Of-Contents":{"title":"Swift Package iOS Tutorial","url":"\/tutorials\/table-of-contents","role":"overview","abstract":[{"text":"Discovering a new framework can be exciting and scary. Learn how you can embed and use OUDS Swift Package.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"With this tutorial you will learn fundamental concepts of Orange Unified Design System and discover the layers of this framework."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Theme, components, tokens… everything will be introduced!"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents","kind":"overview"},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/OUDSThemesContract/tutorial-5-styl